10: Why must you always be like this?
17:
Maybe now's not the best time to
argue...
21:
Hey, you okay? You're not hurt, are
you?
25:
Oh, yes! Thanks to you, I'm right as
rain!
28:
I'd been gathering herbs when those
Walking Stumps came out of
nowhere—oh, but where are my
manners? I'm Ariel. Pleased to make
your acquaintance.
33:
You dwell in this woodland realm, do
you not?
36:
I am Lilith Stratos, head of the
Resistance.
40:
The Resistance? You mean that
force that's fighting beyond our
borders?
43:
Yes, but war is not our sole affair.
That is what I came to discuss.
46:
Ariel, we seek an audience with the
leader of your people. Will you not
act as our guide?
51:
Oh, please, lift your head! You're
royalty!
55:
I'm more than happy to help, you
know. And I'm certain the great ones
will be anxious to learn of your plight.
57:
Not to mention, I would appreciate
company on the way home...
61:
Glad there aren't ONLY assholes
living here.
70:
Well, follow me! And, er... Since we'll
be walking together a while, would
you mind telling me about the
outside world?
86:
It is silent as the grave... You have
led us astray!
90:
This is a place of eternal night. Here
sleep the great ones... also known as
the high elves.
92:
It's also the source of the barrier that
protects this forest.
95:
In plainer terms, however, you might
call this locale a graveyard. A nest
for cowards who hid their faces
from the light so that they could be
blind to change.
98: Why have you brought us here?
102:
To break the barrier, of course. It
should hardly pose a challenge to
you.
105:
Isn't that right, Stella... Keeper of
Starview Village.
110:
Save your questions, and prepare
for battle!
115:
Now, let's see just how powerful you
really are.
